    {
        "sha": "aa186fae77fac3c99a38d3d8d4f0f3907915836a",
        "author": "Alex Newman",
        "email": "thedotmack@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-07-13T03:13:19Z",
        "message": "fix(cloud-sync): guard prompt stamps against mid-flight memory id registration\n\nA prompt SELECTed with the fallback mapping could have its memory id\nregister while the POST was in flight: requeuePromptSync no-ops (the row's\nsynced_at is still NULL) and the unconditional stamp then marked the stale\nfallback upload as synced — permanently mis-keyed in the cloud.\n\nThe stamp for prompts now re-checks, per row, that the mapping pushed is\nstill the current one (SQLite IS so NULLs match for orphan and\nunregistered rows). A row that fails the guard stays unsynced and the same\ndrain loop immediately re-pushes it with the registered mapping; the\nserver upsert on (user_id, device_id, local_id) overwrites in place.\n\nRegression test holds the POST open with a gated fetch, lands the memory\nid mid-flight, and asserts the re-push; mutation-tested by disabling the\nguard (test fails, catching the exact race). Reported by greptile on PR\n#3182 with a reproducing harness.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
        "url": "https://github.com/thedotmack/claude-mem/commit/aa186fae77fac3c99a38d3d8d4f0f3907915836a"
    },
